Nooo, I screamed as the blood gushed out of my body. My gut felt burning hot, then cold, then the coldness spread, the heat leaking out with the blood. I looked at my giant hands, once reknown as the strongest hands in the kingdom, now turning shriveled and blue. What went wrong, I thought, things used to be so simple, so peaceful when we had food, when our countrymen weren't slaughtering each other. 
